24 August 2015 On Monday, 24 August at 12h00, The Minister of Home Affairs Malusi Gigaba will update the media on the progress made regarding the Zimbabwean Special Permit (ZSP). The briefing will be held at Home Affairs Department, 909 Arcardia Street, Hatfield, Pretoria. On Tuesday, 25 August, The Statistician-General Pali Lehohla will release the Economic and Service Delivery Indicators on Mining Production and Sales June 2015 at 10h30, Gross Domestic Product, 2nd Quarter 2015 at 11h00 and the Non-Financial Census of Municipalities for the year ended June 2014 at 13h00. The briefing will be held at Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria with a link up to Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town. On Wednesday, 26 August at 12h00, The Deputy Minister of International Relations and Cooperation Luwellyn Landers will brief the media on international developments. The briefing will be held at Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town with a link up to Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria. Full details will be communicated through a media advisory during the week. On Thursday, 27 August , The Minister in the Presidency for Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation Jeff Radebe will address media on the outcome of the Cabinet meeting to be held on Wednesday, 26 August 2015. Full details will be communicated through a media advisory during the week. In addition to these media briefings, ministers participate in various public events. For a comprehensive list of national and provincial government events visit www.gov.za. Should there be changes in the information above, members of the media will be notified accordingly. Enquiries: Themba Sepotokele Cell: 082 490 9869Issued by Government Communication and Information System